Northampton Beats Perpignan 23-7, Meets Leinster in Heineken Cup Final

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-05-01T16:26:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-01/northampton-beats-perpignan-23-7-meets-leinster-in-heineken-cup-final.html
Northampton beat Perpignan 23-7 today
to reach the final of European rugby’s Heineken Cup where it
will play Leinster.  Ben Foden and Jon Clarke scored tries for the Saints,
Stephen Myler kicking 13 points in the match at  Milton Keynes .
The French club’s points came from a try by Guilhem Guirado
converted by Jerome Porical.  Leinster, the 2009 winner, yesterday beat defending
champion Toulouse 32-23 to advance to the final in Cardiff on
May 21.  Jamie Heaslip and Brian O’Driscoll scored tries and Jonathan
Sexton kicked 22 points in Dublin as Leinster avenged a loss to
Toulouse in last year’s semifinals. Northampton won the
tournament in 2000.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty in London at 
